Coronavirusâ€™ reach from beyond the grave: Deceased body transmits COVID-19 It's technically possible to catch COVID-19 from the dead.
Indeed, researchers are learning new things about the novel coronavirus almost daily, the most recent lesson coming from beyond the grave.
Scientists in Thailand have reported the first known case of COVID-19 infection from a dead person.
The deceased was a forensic medical professional.
Data regarding the exact number of COVID-19 contaminated corpses is not easy to come by since testing for COVID-19 in dead bodies is not routine.